-- Kuwait Finance House CEO steps down - sources
-- By Ahmed Hagagy
-- Thu Apr 24, 2014 06:18AM EDT
-- None



KUWAIT, April 24 (Reuters) - The chief executive of Kuwait Finance House <KFIN.KW>, the Gulf state's largest Islamic lender, has stepped down, two company sources said on Thursday.

Mohammed al-Omar's resignation as CEO is linked to wider management changes at KFH, one of the sources said.